ges of rolled out dough. Starting from a long edge, tightly roll up dough into a log."},{"content":"Slice long roll into 2 cm thick pieces then join them together on one of the prepared baking trays in the shape of a snail. Set aside and repeat with remaining dough and herb butter, creating another snail on second prepared tray."},{"content":"Cover with cling film and leave in a warm place until doubled in size (approx. 1 hour). Towards the end of this time, preheat oven to 190°C."},{"content":"Bake for 12-15 minutes (190°C) until golden brown. Serve warm at the table."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Use the end pieces of the cut rolls to create the eye stalks and tail as these pieces tend to be slightly smaller."],"basicInfo":["easy","30m","2h 45m","50 pieces"]}